    </div>

    <div class="ypd-faq">
      <div class="ypd-faq-item is-open">
        <button type="button" class="ypd-faq-question">Are yak chews safe for dogs?<span>+</span></button>
        <div class="ypd-faq-answer">
          Yes, when sized appropriately and given under supervision, they are positioned as a safer alternative to many
          processed chews.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="ypd-faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="ypd-faq-question">How long does one chew last?<span>+</span></button>
        <div class="ypd-faq-answer">
          It depends on dog size and chewing style, but they are designed to last much longer than many everyday chew
          options.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="ypd-faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="ypd-faq-question">Which size should I choose?<span>+</span></button>
        <div class="ypd-faq-answer">Use the size guide above and size up if your dog is between weight ranges.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="ypd-faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="ypd-faq-question">What do I do with the leftover end piece?<span>+</span></button>
        <div class="ypd-faq-answer">Soak it, microwave it, cool it, and turn it into a crunchy puff treat.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

